Tutorial 9/10 ð

To Add This Cut Out Effect in VN video editor â¤µï¸

1. Open your project in VN video editor.

2. Import the main video clip onto the timeline.

3. Then select the âFreezeâ Option It will automatically take a Screenshot of a Frame as a base Layer

4. Then Select the âForward â Option to Make it as a PIP Layer

5. Select the âCutoutâ Option and then Remove the Background To Separate the Object 

6. Then Trim the layer to 0.30 Secs 

7. Add Two Keyframes One in the start of the Layer 
And One Keyframe in The End .

8. Then go to the keyframe which we have added  in start of layer Place the cutout, from where you  want to have this effect 

For eg: In i have placed towards top of the frame

And you are done !!

Hope you learned something newð»

List â¬ï¸
.
1) VN (for reel edits)
My absolute favourite for editing reels. You can create 3 layer videos and videos with sliding clips on VN. The interface is quite beginner friendly. In-app ads are short & tolerable (the best part) and itâs watermark free.
.
2) ProCCD (for digital camera template)
Has filters with frames of digital cameras as template. Recreates the look of those vintage digital cameras.
.
3) Dazzcam (for retro filters)
This has the best looking retro filters I have seen, clean and realistic. Itâs not available for android unfortunately.
.
4) Unfold (for fonts and templates)
Helps create the most visually pleasing and aesthetic stories with templates and fonts. 
.
5) Picsart (for hand drawn fonts)
This one lets you draw your own texts and use in reels.
.
6) Prequel (unique filters)
Provides a lot of interesting filters that I haven't found elsewhere. Most of their features are free!
